titleStmt.title: Cambridge, Cambridge University Library, MS Or.476

respStmt.resp: Edited by Michael Marx in collaboration with Tobias J. Jocham et. al. TEI version created by Yasmin Faghihi and Huw Jones

summary.p: 52 folios; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: MS Or. 476; Qurʾānic text: Q 14:27-52, Q 15:9-99, Q 16:1-61, Q 16:96-122, Q 16:127-128, Q 17:1-4, Q 17:37-63, Q 17:68-107, Q 18:2-27, Q 18:30-74; 7 Lines per page; Dimensions: 198 x 120mm; Script style: new style I; Estimated date of production: 10th or 11th century AD /4th or 5th century Hijri.

Fragment of an Abbasid Qur'ān probably written in the third or fourth century H. / ninth or tenth century C.E, containing verses 27-52 from Sura al-Ibrāhīm (سورة ابراهيم); verses 9-99 fom Sura al-Ḥijr (سورة الحجر); verses 1-61 and 96-128 from Sura al-Naḥl (سورة النحل); verses 1-4, 37-63, and 68-107 from Sura al-Isrāʾ (سورة الإسراء); and verses 1-27 and 30-74 from Sura al-Kahf (سورة الكهف). For more information about the manuscript, see the entry in the Digital Library of Cambridge University.
